RabbitMQ doesn't propagate W3C trace context automatically. You must **inject** the current `Activity` context into message headers when publishing and **extract** it when consuming.

### Publisher (Service A)

```csharp
using System.Diagnostics;

// Create an ActivitySource for your app
static readonly ActivitySource Source = new("ServiceA");

// When publishing:
using var activity = Source.StartActivity("OrderPublished", ActivityKind.Producer);

var props = channel.CreateBasicProperties();
props.Headers ??= new Dictionary<string, object>();

// Inject trace context into message headers
if (Activity.Current != null)
{
    props.Headers["traceparent"] = Activity.Current.Id;
    props.Headers["tracestate"]  = Activity.Current.TraceStateString ?? "";
}

channel.BasicPublish(exchange, routingKey, props, body);
```

### Consumer (Service B)

```csharp
static readonly ActivitySource Source = new("ServiceB");

// In your consumer callback:
var headers = ea.BasicProperties.Headers;
string? traceparent = null;
string? tracestate  = null;

if (headers?.TryGetValue("traceparent", out var tp) == true)
    traceparent = Encoding.UTF8.GetString((byte[])tp);
if (headers?.TryGetValue("tracestate", out var ts) == true)
    tracestate = Encoding.UTF8.GetString((byte[])ts);

// Parse the remote context and start a linked child activity
ActivityContext parentCtx = default;
if (traceparent != null)
    ActivityContext.TryParse(traceparent, tracestate, out parentCtx);

using var activity = Source.StartActivity(
    "OrderReceived",
    ActivityKind.Consumer,
    parentContext: parentCtx   // ← links this span to Service A's trace
);
```

### Wire it up in `Program.cs` (both services)

```csharp
builder.Services.AddOpenTelemetry()
    .WithTracing(t => t
        .AddSource("ServiceA")   // or "ServiceB"
        .AddAspNetCoreInstrumentation()
        .AddOtlpExporter());     // Jaeger, Zipkin, etc.
```

### Why this works

| Concept | Detail |
|---|---|
| `traceparent` header | Carries the trace ID + parent span ID (W3C format) |
| `ActivityKind.Producer/Consumer` | Tells the exporter this is a messaging span |
| `parentContext:` | Creates a parent-child relationship across the queue boundary |

### Tip — MassTransit / NServiceBus

If you switch to **MassTransit** or **NServiceBus**, this propagation is built-in — they inject/extract `traceparent` automatically. With raw `RabbitMQ.Client`, you must do it manually as shown above.
